d constitutes a\nBerezinskii-Kosterlitz-Thouless phase transition. The model also features a\ndirect phase transition from the most ordered state to the most disordered\nstate, and this transition is neither in the 2D XY nor in the 3D XY\nuniversality class. It comes about via a simultaneous proliferation of point\nvortices in two spatial dimensions and $\\Delta \\theta$-instantons, with a\ncomplicated interplay between them.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jun 2012 20:00:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-06-27"}
