-interacting walk with a fixed number of particles\ncan distinguish all SRGs, thus demonstrating a potential fundamental difference\nbetween the distinguishing power of interacting and noninteracting walks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jun 2012 04:45:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Jun 2012 19:01:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-08-27"}
